    "stat_block": {
        "type": "stat_block",
        "subtype": "equipment",
        "text": "The serrated blade of this *+1 striking dagger* has a greenish tinge, and the hilt is sculpted to look like the head of a serpent about to strike. When you critically succeed at an attack roll with the serpent dagger, the target becomes sickened 1 unless it succeeds at a DC 19 Fortitude save. This is a poison effect. In addition, you can activate the dagger to poison a creature with a more potent poison.",
        "level": 5,
